Israeli Stocks: Ness Technologies, Perrigo and Pluristem

-- B y   R o n i t   G o o d m a n
-- 
2011-04-13T14:25:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/israeli-stocks-brack-capital-properties-perrigo-and-scailex.html
Israel ’s TA-25 Index was little
changed, dropping less than 0.1 percent to 1,330.73 at the 4:30
p.m. close in  Tel Aviv . Investors traded about 1.96 billion
shekels ($574 million) in shares and convertible securities.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Ness Technologies Inc. (NSTC)   climbed the most since
April 3, advancing 2.1 percent to 22.93 shekels. The computer-
service provider won a 60 million shekels contract from Israel
Electric Corp. to implement SAP-based projects.  Perrigo Co. (PRGO)   increased to the highest level since
the shares listed in Tel Aviv in 2005, gaining 1.1 percent to
295.80 shekels. The U.S.  Food and Drug Administration  concluded
a re-inspection of the maker of over-the-counter drugs’ Allegan
facility and informed the company that it has an acceptable
regulatory status.  Separately, Goldman, Sachs & Co. raised its recommendation
on the shares to “neutral” from “sell.”  Pluristem Therapeutics Inc. (PSTI)   jumped to the highest
since Feb. 7, advancing 4.6 percent to 10.89 shekels. The
developer of cell-therapy products said follow-ups to clinical
trials showed “encouraging” results for the treatment of
critical limb ischemia.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ronit Goodman in Tel Aviv at 
 rgoodman9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  